{
  "document_id": "job-31",
  "title": "Job 31",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "“I have made a covenant with my eyes;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "What would be my portion from God above"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Does not calamity befall the unrighteous"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Does he not see my ways"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "“If I have walked with falsehood,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "let me be weighed in a just balance,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "if my step has turned aside from the way,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "then let me sow and another eat,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "“If my heart has been enticed by a woman"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "then let my wife grind for another,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "For that would be a heinous crime;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "for that would be a fire consuming down to Abaddon,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "“If I have rejected the cause of my male or female slaves,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "what then shall I do when God rises up?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Did not he who made me in the womb make them?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "“If I have withheld anything that the poor desired"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "or have eaten my morsel alone"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "for from my youth I reared the orphan like a father,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "if I have seen anyone perish for lack of clothing"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "whose loins have not blessed me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "if I have raised my hand against the orphan"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "then let my shoulder blade fall from my shoulder,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "For I was in terror of calamity from God,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "“If I have made gold my trust"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "if I have rejoiced because my wealth was great"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "if I have looked at the sun when it shone"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "and my heart has been secretly enticed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "this also would be an iniquity to be punished by the judges,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "“If I have rejoiced at the ruin of those who hated me"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "I have not let my mouth sin"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "if those of my tent ever said,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "the stranger has not lodged in the street;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "if I have concealed my transgressions as others do,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "because I stood in great fear of the multitude,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "O that I had one to hear me!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "Surely I would carry it on my shoulder;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "I would give him an account of all my steps;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "“If my land has cried out against me"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-39",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 39,
      "text": "if I have eaten its yield without payment"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-31-40",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 40,
      "text": "let thorns grow instead of wheat"
    }
  ]
}